.TH minios-kernel 1 "August 2025" "MiniOS Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
minios-kernel \- Command-line tool for packaging MiniOS kernels
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B minios-kernel
 --source-repo <package-name> --output-dir <path> [options]
.br
.B minios-kernel
 --source-deb <deb-file> --output-dir <path> [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B minios-kernel
 is a command-line utility that handles the core tasks of packaging a Linux kernel for use with the MiniOS distribution. It extracts the kernel and modules, generates an initramfs, and creates a SquashFS image.
.PP
This tool is the backend for the graphical Bminios-kernel-managerR but can be used directly for scripting or advanced tasks. It requires one source argument (B--source-repoR or B--source-debR) and the output directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR "--source-repo " <package-name>
Specify the name of the kernel package to be downloaded from the APT repository (e.g., Ilinux-image-6.5.0-10-genericR).
.TP
.BR "--source-deb " <deb-file>
Specify the path to a local .deb file for the kernel package.
.TP
.BR "--output-dir " <path>
Required. Specify the directory where the packaged kernel files (vmlinuz, initrfs, and SquashFS module) will be saved.
.TP
.BR "--squashfs-comp " <compression>
Set the compression method for the SquashFS image. Defaults to BzstdR. Common options include BgzipR, Blz4R, and BxzR.
.TP
.BR "--initrd-comp " <compression>
Set the compression method for the initramfs. Defaults to BzstdR. Common options include BgzipR, Blz4R, and BxzR.
